<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Ranvir Singh and Alex Beresford get to grips with koalas and anteaters in their new ITV series All Around Britain. </p>

<p>Every week, the Good Morning Britain hosts will present the show from some of the country’s most popular attractions and famous landmarks and discover their lesser-known stories. </p>

<p>For the first episode, set to air on Sunday morning, Ranvir, 43, and Alex, 39, head to Longleat Safari Park in Wiltshire.  </p>

<p>New show: Ranvir Singh and Alex Beresford get to grips with koalas and anteaters in their new ITV series All Around Britain</p>

<p>They joined keepers to feed the koalas, sea lions and giraffes. </p>

<p>The duo rolled up their sleeves to help prepare food for the park's twelve hundred residents, including mixing an insect porridge to feed a hungry anteater, which included plenty of mealworms and termites. </p>

<p>Alex told MailOnline: 'We had a fun day filming the first episode of the new series at Longleat earlier this week. We met some koalas and fed the anteaters.</p>

<p>Interesting: Every week, the Good Morning Britain hosts will present the show from some of the country’s most popular attractions and famous landmarks</p>

<p>Animals: For the first episode, set to air on Sunday morning, Ranvir, 43, and Alex, 39, head to Longleat Safari Park in Wiltshire</p>

<p>'I did have one moment of horror where I spilt some of the anteater porridge down my top. That was pretty disgusting. </p>

<p>'It had meal worms, bugs and fruit in it. Ranvir also fed some hungry giraffes and it was amazing to meet some of the animals.</p>

<p>'Our new show kicks off on Sunday on ITV at 11.20am and we're really looking forward to it. </p>

<p>Preparations: They joined keepers to feed the koalas, sea lions and giraffes</p>

<p>''It's a mix of us presenting from different locations and there will also be stories coming from across the UK too.'</p>

<p>It comes as Ranvir was announced as part of the Strictly Come Dancing line-up earlier this week. </p>

<p>Ranvir joins the likes of former NFL star Jason Bell, The Wanted singer Max George and actress Caroline Quentin. </p>

<p>Watch All Around Britain, starting this Sunday at 11.20am on ITV.</p>

